"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638382","Department of Health","false","2016-11-25","<p>The Department’s Female Genital Mutilation (FGM) Prevention programme is continuing its work with NHS England and across the health service to tackle FGM. Launched in 2014 with total funding of over £4 million the programme has delivered training and outreach nationally reaching thousands of National Health Service professionals, introduced data collection and statistics, and developed policy and guidance on safeguarding and commissioning services. The programme in 2016/17 is focussing on the mental health needs of survivors and on embedding change across the NHS.</p><p> </p><p>Last year the Department commissioned Health Education England to develop a range of FGM e-learning sessions available free of charge to NHS staff. These sessions include training on the mandatory reporting duty.</p><p> </p><p>As part of the Department’s FGM Prevention Programme an FGM Mandatory Reporting awareness pack was sent to all hospitals and general practitioner practices in February 2016. In addition, the Department has worked with partners to support them in hosting articles and awareness raising information; one example of this was the provision of a flyer insert about the new FGM mandatory reporting duty which was included in the Royal College of Midwives (RCM) magazine, sent to approximately 45,000 RCM members.</p><p> </p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-11-25T14:34:49.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638382/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638382/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638382/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-11-17","Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to make training on how to respond to cases of female genital mutilation mandatory for all doctors, nurses and medical staff.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","53567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638383","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Home Office does not hold data centrally on these costs. It is a matter for Police and Crime Commissioners to make decisions around appointing, suspending and removing chief constables.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-23T16:40:19.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638383/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638383/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638383/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Police: Termination of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the total spent by police forces on compensation, legal fees and other expenses related to the termination of the employment of chief constables since the introduction of police and crime cmmissioners.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","53579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638384","Home Office","false","2016-12-21","<p>Detention costs over the past three financial years have been published in the Home Office’s Annual Report and Accounts, for 2015-16 and 2014-15. Copies of these publications can be found on the .gov.uk website:</p><p>For 2015-16: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf</p><p>For 2014-15: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/441282/HO-AR15_web.pdf</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-21T11:01:57.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638384/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638384/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638384/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the cost of immigration detention was in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","53575"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638385","Home Office","false","2017-04-20","<p>There is always a presumption of liberty and detention is only ever used sparingly and for the shortest period necessary. For those individuals with no right to remain in the UK, we expect them to leave the country of their own volition and the Home Office has programmes to support voluntary return.</p><p>The Home Office expects that current and planned reforms, and broader changes in legislation, policy and operational approaches will lead to a reduction in the number of the most vulnerable detained and the duration of detention before removal.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","53631","2017-04-20T08:29:16.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638385/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638385/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638385/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Alternatives to Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department plans to develop and implement community-based alternatives to detention for (a) vulnerable people who have already been detained and (b) people at risk of vulnerability as a result of detention.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","53576"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638386","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Home Office does not hold data centrally on the number of detentions of children made for non-payment of fines. The Home Office collect and publish data on the number of persons detained for more than 24 hours under part IV of the Police and Criminal Evidence (PACE) Act broken down by the length of detention and police force area.</p><p>These data cannot be broken down by age or to identify those arrested or detained for non-payment of fines. The available data are published here:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-23T16:40:40.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638386/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638386/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Police Custody: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many times children have been detained overnight in police custody for non-payment of fines in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Christina Rees","Neath","Christina Rees","53546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638387","Home Office","false","2016-11-22","<p>The information requested is published in table dt_11_q (detention data tables) in ‘Immigration Statistics, April - June 2016’, available from the Home Office website at: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/546763/detention-q2-2016-tabs.ods</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-22T17:13:36.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638387/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638387/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638387/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people are held in immigration detention who have been detained for (a) less than three months, (b) between three months and one year, (c) between one year and three years and (d) for more than three years.","false","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","53574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638388","Home Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>At every step of the negotiations to leave the EU we will work to ensure the best possible outcome for the British people.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","53518","2016-11-24T12:11:46.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638388/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638388/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Free Movement of People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what discussions she has had with her EU counterparts on maintaining visa free, free travel to EU countries after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638389","Home Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>At every step of the negotiations to leave the EU we will work to ensure the best possible outcome for the British people.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","53517","2016-11-24T12:11:46.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638389/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638389/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638389/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Free Movement of People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she has taken to ensure that visa free travel to EU countries is maintained after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53518"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638390","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The UK will in due course be leaving the EU but the importance of law enforcement co-operation with our EU and global allies has not changed. We are exploring options for cooperation arrangements once the UK has left the EU. We will do what is necessary to keep people safe, but it would be wrong to set out unilateral positions on specific measures in advance of negotiations.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-23T16:36:19.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638390/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638390/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Law and Order","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of the UK's decision to leave the EU on law enforcement and security in the UK.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","53508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638391","Home Office","false","2016-12-09","<p>The Home Secretary engages regularly with a wide range of stakeholders to ensure that our law enforcement agencies are able to undertake effectively their core function of protecting the public. As more and more communications take place online, this of course includes providers of telecommunications services such as social media companies.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-12-09T16:15:08.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638391/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638391/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638391/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Social Media: Criminal Investigation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she has had discussions with social media companies on improving their cooperation with police investigations.","false","Biography information for Tom Blenkinsop","Middlesbrough South and East Cleveland","Tom Blenkinsop","53500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638392","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>All training and assistance provided by or on behalf of Her Majesty's Government complies with our international human rights policies and obligations.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-11-23T16:41:14.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638392/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638392/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Police: Bahrain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 18 October 2016 to Question 46877, whether UK police advice and assistance has included training in human rights.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","53668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638393","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Home Office does not hold information on the number of people who have had assets frozen or asset recovered by the categories described in the question. Furthermore, the nationality of the individual is not routinely recorded.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","53659 ; 53660","2016-11-23T17:11:10.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638393/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638393/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Freezing of Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people, by nationality, suspected by UK law enforcement of involvement in (a) organised crime, (b) financial crime or (c) serious human rights abuses have been subject to (i) asset freezes or (ii) asset recoveries by the Government in each of the last eight years.","false","Biography information for Dominic Raab","Esher and Walton","Mr Dominic Raab","53661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638394","Home Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>The UK is willing and committed to helping international partners and will consider any request on a case by case basis. However as a matter of longstanding policy and practice the Home Office can neither confirm nor deny the existence, content or status of any individual request.</p><p>Where any criminal allegation is made the relevant authorities will investigate as appropriate. It is not the position of the Home Office to comment on individual complaints.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-11-24T18:34:21.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638394/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638394/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/638394/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-17","Kyrgyzstan: Proceeds of Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if the Government will investigate whether any stolen Kyrgyz state funds ended up in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","53669"
