"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637781","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-30","<p>These schemes are under investigation by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC). Penalties are in place for those caught attempting to avoid tax by using an avoidance scheme. This includes promoters of such schemes who can face fines of up to £1 million for failing to notify an avoidance scheme under the Disclosure of Tax Avoidance Schemes regime.</p><p> </p><p>In the last two years, HMRC has secured an additional £5.5 billion through targeting tax avoidance schemes<em>.</em> The Chancellor of the Exchequer announced in the Autumn Statement 2016 that the Government will counter abuse of the VAT Flat Rate Scheme while keeping VAT accounting simple for the small businesses that use the scheme as intended.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2016-11-30T14:20:45.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637781/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637781/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-16","Tax Avoidance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they have taken to prevent the use of aggressive tax avoidance schemes under which employers reduce their national insurance payments and exploit VAT rules designed to benefit very small businesses; and with what results.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL3294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637782","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-11-30","<p>There are no plans to change the current approach of reporting details of Ministers' meetings on a quarterly basis.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-11-30T13:35:20.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637782/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637782/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-11-16","Brexit","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Bridges of Headley on 3 November (HL2764), whether they will exceptionally publish on a weekly basis details of ministerial meetings relating to Brexit until Article 50 has been invoked.","false","Biography information for Lord Brooke of Alverthorpe",,"Lord Brooke of Alverthorpe","HL3295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637783","Department for Education","false","2016-11-24","<p>The collection of pupil-level data via the school census supports the drive to raise standards, provide accurate targeted funding, and the monitoring and development of policy. Without this evidence and data, we cannot have a clear picture of how the school system is working or ensure that no groups of children are missing out on the education they deserve.</p><p> </p><p>The new data items on nationality, country of birth and English proficiency will be used to help us better understand how children, with for example, English as an additional language, perform in terms of their broader education, and to assess and monitor the scale and impact immigration may be having on the schools’ sector. The collection of these data items is completely optional and parents are under no obligation to provide it if they do not want to.</p><p> </p><p>This information is collected via the school census on a termly basis. If parents have previously provided this information to schools and now wish to retract it, they should inform the school of this decision. For such cases, schools can update their systems to show a parent has refused to provide the information and this will be collected within the next school census, which is due on the 19<sup>th</sup> January.</p><p> </p><p>Where a parent has exercised this right, the Department will remove any information collected on country of birth and nationality during the autumn census.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash",,"2016-11-24T11:23:10.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637783/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637783/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-16","Schools: Census","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the remarks by Lord Nash on 31 October (HL Deb, col 510), whether they have given any further consideration to allowing parents the ability to retract information on the birthplace and nationality of their children from the school census.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Clancarty",,"The Earl of Clancarty","HL3296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637784","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-29","<p>We are concerned by the decisions of the Republic of South Africa, Burundi and The Gambia to withdraw from the Rome Statute. The UK recognises the need for dialogue with States Parties and we took part in meetings in the margins of the Annual Assembly of States Parties in The Hague between 16 -24 November. Our High Commissioner in South Africa has had a number of discussions with senior officials about South African withdrawal.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-11-29T15:31:56.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637784/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637784/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-16","Africa: International Criminal Court","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to those African nations which have made statements regarding their withdrawal from the International Criminal Court.","true","Biography information for Baroness Helic",,"Baroness Helic","HL3297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637785","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-22","<p>The Government intends to publish a discussion paper on options for improving corporate governance before the end of the year.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-11-22T14:45:48.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637785/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637785/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637785/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-16","Business: Regulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the answer by Baroness Neville-Rolfe on 8 September (HL Deb, cols 1125–6), when they intend to publish the consultation document setting out a range of options for improving corporate governance.","false","Biography information for Lord Hodgson of Astley Abbotts",,"Lord Hodgson of Astley Abbotts","HL3298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637786","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-11-22","<p>We expect the Each Home Counts Review by Dr Peter Bonfield to be published soon.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-11-22T14:41:54.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637786/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637786/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637786/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-11-16","Consumer Advice, Protection, Standards and Enforcement for Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy Independent Review","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they plan to publish the review by Dr Peter Bonfield into consumer advice, protection, standards and enforcement for energy efficiency and renewable energy.","false","Biography information for Lord Stunell",,"Lord Stunell","HL3299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637787","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-28","<p>The National Citizen Service (NCS) Bill and accompanying Royal Charter are designed to give the NCS Trust a new legal framework. Under the charter, the NCS Trust will have the freedom to determine its own contracting arrangements with delivery partners to achieve its objectives. Government will hold the NCS Trust to account for the outcomes it delivers.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ashton of Hyde",,"2016-11-28T16:24:27.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637787/answer","Biography information for Lord Ashton of Hyde","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637787/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637787/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-16","Voluntary Work: Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they plan to take to safeguard the future funding of small scale deliverers of the National Citizen Service when establishing its Royal Charter.","false","Biography information for Lord Stunell",,"Lord Stunell","HL3300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637788","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-29","<p>I refer the Noble Lord to the Written Ministerial Statement (attached) made by the Minister of Housing on 21 November in the other place (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2016-11-21/HCWS274/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2016-11-21/HCWS274/</a>) and repeated in this House.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-11-29T15:51:45.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637788/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637788/answer","161129  WMS - Social Housing - HL3301.pdf","161129  WMS - Social Housing - HL3301.pdf","Social Housing WMS - HCWS274","Social Housing WMS - HCWS274","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637788/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-16","Social Rented Housing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they expect the Pay to Stay working group to next meet; and whether they expect that the implementation date for Pay to Stay will be April 2017.","true","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL3301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637789","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-28","<p>We remain committed to the Voluntary Right to Buy for housing association tenants. The Government is continuing to work closely with the National Housing Federation and the housing association sector on the implementation of the main scheme and will announce more details in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-11-28T15:13:09.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637789/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637789/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-16","Right to Buy Scheme: Housing Associations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they expect Right to Buy to be available to housing association tenants.","true","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL3302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637790","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-29","<p>The provisions in the Housing and Planning Act 2016 relating to the sale of vacant higher value local authority housing came into force on Royal Assent. However there is a number of steps that must be taken before local authorities will be required to make payments to Government under these powers. This includes making regulations defining higher value, which will be subject to the affirmative procedure, and consulting before making a determination. Further information will be shared in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2016-11-29T15:32:32.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637790/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637790/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637790/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-16","Right to Buy Scheme: Housing Associations","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when the provisions of the Housing and Planning Act 2016 relating to the higher value levy will come into force.","true","Biography information for Lord Kennedy of Southwark",,"Lord Kennedy of Southwark","HL3303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637791","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-11-28","<p>As I have previously explained to the Noble Lord, this Government understands the concept of parity of esteem, as set out in the 1998 Belfast Agreement, as relating to and placing a general obligation on the UK Government to treat people of different traditions or communities in Northern Ireland fairly and with equal respect. The Belfast Agreement makes no distinction between communities and individuals.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2016-11-28T14:43:15.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637791/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637791/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637791/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-11-16","Belfast Agreement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Dunlop on 15 November (HL2983), whether parity of esteem applies only to individuals, and not to communities.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL3304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637792","Department for Education","false","2016-11-30","<p>The criteria used for three-year allocations for 2017/18 were published in “The allocation of Initial Teacher Training Places 2017-18” on 29 September. The four criteria used were: average degree class of trainees, quality of training measured by OFSTED, quality of outcomes measured by employment into the maintained sector, and recruitment performance against allocations.</p><p>We will be publishing the full list of providers eligible for three-year allocations, and the allocations by subject in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","HL3306","2016-11-30T17:57:59.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637792/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637792/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637792/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-16","Teachers: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the funding allocations to initial teacher training courses for 2017–18 apportioned by (1) primary phase, and (2) each secondary subject, broken down by (a) higher education, (b) school-centred initial teacher training (SCITT), (c) School Direct fee paying with higher education institutions (HEI) partners, (d) School Direct fee paying with SCITT partners, (e) School Direct salaried with HEI partners, and (f) School Direct salaried with SCITT partners.","false","Biography information for Baroness Donaghy",,"Baroness Donaghy","HL3305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637793","Department for Education","false","2016-11-30","<p>The criteria used for three-year allocations for 2017/18 were published in “The allocation of Initial Teacher Training Places 2017-18” on 29 September. The four criteria used were: average degree class of trainees, quality of training measured by OFSTED, quality of outcomes measured by employment into the maintained sector, and recruitment performance against allocations.</p><p>We will be publishing the full list of providers eligible for three-year allocations, and the allocations by subject in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Nash","HL3305","2016-11-30T17:57:59.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637793/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637793/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637793/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-11-16","Teachers: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which higher education institutions and school-centred initial teacher training providers received three year allocations for 2017–18 onwards; and what criteria were used to identify such providers.","false","Biography information for Baroness Donaghy",,"Baroness Donaghy","HL3306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637813","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-24","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-24T17:31:59.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637813/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637813/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637813/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-16","Treasury: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many times his Department has (a) terminated a contract, (b) imposed a penalty and (c) denied permission for a company to tender on the grounds of grave professional misconduct since November 2015.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","53202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637814","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-21","<p>On 7 October the Chancellor announced that the Government would begin to sell its remaining stake in Lloyds via a trading plan, withdrawing the retail sale. Retail investors, like any other investor, will be able to buy shares in Lloyds by purchasing shares via a stockbroker.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-11-21T15:17:19.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637814/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637814/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637814/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-16","Lloyds Banking Group","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the timetable is for offering the retail sale of Lloyds Banking Group shares to the public in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","53207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637815","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-21","<p>Reliable estimates are not available of the potential annual administrative impact resulting from a decision to combine national insurance and income tax deductions for those on PAYE.</p><p> </p><p>The Office for Tax Simplification (OTS) recently published a report, on 14 November, regarding closer alignment of income tax and National Insurance Contributions (NICs). Whilst the OTS did not produce cost estimates, their report highlighted a number of areas that would impact on the administrative burdens for HM Revenue and Customs as a result of combining deductions for NICs and income tax. This is summarised in paragraph 2.100 of the OTS publication, which is available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/567491/OTS_report_web_final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/567491/OTS_report_web_final.pdf</a>.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-21T16:58:36.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637815/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637815/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637815/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-16","PAYE","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an estimate of the potential annual administrative savings resulting from a decision to combine national insurance and income tax deductions for those on PAYE.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","53208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637816","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-24","<p>In respect of media management and campaign communications, the Treasury’s communications team monitors relevant publicly available social media content to evaluate the effectiveness of Government campaigns. The Treasury follows Government Communications Service (GCS) Standards using the GCS Evaluation Framework https://gcs.civilservice.gov.uk/guidance/evaluation/tools-and-resources/</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-11-24T17:21:50.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637816/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637816/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637816/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-16","Treasury: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department is monitoring content that is publicly available on social networking sites using overt monitoring techniques.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","53235"
