"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637942","Home Office","false","2016-11-21","<p>The Department's portfolio of digital and technology projects is subject to rolling review against government priorities and funding availability. Projects are also subject to regular assurance reviews as part of corporate governance. We have no current plans to cancel specific projects.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-21T16:47:18.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637942/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637942/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Home Office: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of her Department's digital and IT projects are (a) under review and (b) subject to probable cancellation.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","53176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637943","Home Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>The Home Office has terminated one (1) contract since November 2015. This contract was terminated by mutual agreement with the supplier not because of poor performance but because a different replacement contract was required to support the change in project requirements.</p><p>The Department is not aware of any providers being denied opportunities to bid as a result of grave misconduct.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-24T17:40:29.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637943/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637943/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Home Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many times her Department has (a) terminated a contract, (b) imposed a penalty and (c) denied permission for a company to tender on the grounds of grave professional misconduct since November 2015.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","53199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637944","Home Office","false","2016-12-21","<p>We will in due course specify the number of unaccompanied refugee children to be transferred to the UK under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016. Eritrean and Afghan children over the age of 15 do not qualify under the published criteria for the implementation of section 67 in France, because these reflect our focus on the very youngest children, those assessed as being at high risk of sexual exploitation and those likely to be granted refugee status in the UK. The latter criterion is based on nationalities with a first instance asylum grant rate of 75 per cent or higher in the year to June 2016.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","53436","2016-12-21T10:11:53.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637944/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637944/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what progress she has made in making an estimate of how many unaccompanied refugee children will be transferred from the EU to the UK under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","53365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637945","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>Ministers and officials promote the guidance at events on transparency in supply chains and in response to a range of queries from businesses, trade bodies and non-governmental organisations . We have also promoted transparency in supply chains legislation to other governments, both in bilateral meetings and through multilateral fora, including at G7, the Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development and the Organisation for Security and Co-operation in Europe events.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-23T16:44:04.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637945/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637945/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to promote the guidance, Transparency in supply chains: a practical guide, issued under section 54(9) of the Modern Slavery Act 2015.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","53337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637946","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Government has not estimated what proportion of businesses have complied so far. We published guidance in October 2015 advising that businesses should report as soon as reasonably practicable after their financial year end, which in practice should mean within six months of an organisation’s financial year end.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-23T16:44:22.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637946/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637946/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the proportion of businesses with a turnover of £36 million or more which are complying with the provisions of section 54 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015.","false","Biography information for Alison McGovern","Wirral South","Alison McGovern","53319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637947","Home Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>The information requested for the last 5 calendar years is published in table vi_01_q (visa data tables volume 1) in ‘Immigration Statistics, April - June 2016’, available from the Home Office website at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2016/list-of-tables#visas</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-11-24T17:35:49.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637947/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637947/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of visitor visa applications have been refused in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","53344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637948","Home Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>The information requested for the last 5 calendar years is published in table vi_01_q (visa data tables volume 1) in ‘Immigration Statistics, April - June 2016’, available from the Home Office website at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2016/list-of-tables#visas</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-19T16:53:33.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637948/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637948/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many visitor visas have been granted in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","53343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637949","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>Whilst we keep list of proscribed groups under review, we do not routinely comment on whether an organisation is or is not under consideration for proscription.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-11-23T17:11:55.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637949/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637949/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Hezbollah","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will proscribe the political wing of Hezbollah under section 13 of the Terrorism Act 2000.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","53381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637950","Home Office","false","2016-11-24","<p>The following table details spend with each of the publishers named over the last six years. We are interpreting Trinity Mirror as referring to the titles the Daily Mirror, the Sunday Mirror, the Sunday People, the Sunday Mail and the Daily Record only. Please note that that all costs include media, but exclude VAT and fees, and that 2016/17 figures include committed spend to date this financial year.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Trinity Mirror</p></td><td><p>Sunday Times</p></td><td><p>Mail on Sunday</p></td><td><p>The Sun</p></td><td><p>The Sun on Sunday</p></td><td><p>The Huffington Post</p></td><td><p>Mail Online</p></td><td><p>The Daily Mail</p></td><td><p>The Guardian</p></td><td><p>The Times</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>£6,885</p></td><td><p>£9,471</p></td><td><p>£18,139</p></td><td><p>£10,370</p></td><td><p>£9,020</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£27,011</p></td><td><p>£2,057</p></td><td><p>£4,645</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£17,595</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£84,788</p></td><td><p>£51,589</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td><td><p>£0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Spend in the financial year 2014/15 relates to the Modern Slavery marketing campaign which sought to raise awareness of the issue and encourage reporting via a helpline and website. National press partnership activity was used to explain the issue in depth, including the signs of slavery to look out for, to raise awareness and encourage reporting. Spend in the financial year 2016/17 relates to the Fire Kills campaign, which encourages fire safety behaviour and aims to reduce the number of accidental fires in the home and associated deaths and injuries.</p><p>Figures exclude any costs relating to recruitment advertising in the national press as these costs are not centrally held, and collation of this information would be at disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2016-11-24T18:27:34.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637950/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637950/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Home Office: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department spent on advertising in each of the last six years in (a) Trinity Mirror, (b) the Sunday Times, (c) the Mail on Sunday, (d) the Sun, (e) the Sun on Sunday, (f) the Huffington Post, (g) Mail Online, (h) Daily Mail, (i) The Guardian and (j) The Times.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","53249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637951","Home Office","false","2016-11-21","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data biannually on the number of police officers and Police Community Support Officers (PCSOs) employed by each police force. These data can be found in the 'Police Workforce, England and Wales' statistical bulletins. The latest statistics, representing the picture as at 31 March 2016, can be found here:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","53246","2016-11-21T16:18:39.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637951/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637951/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Police: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police officers were employed by North Wales Police in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","53247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637952","Home Office","false","2016-11-21","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data biannually on the number of police officers and Police Community Support Officers (PCSOs) employed by each police force. These data can be found in the 'Police Workforce, England and Wales' statistical bulletins. The latest statistics, representing the picture as at 31 March 2016, can be found here:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/police-workforce-england-and-wales</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","53247","2016-11-21T16:18:39.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637952/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637952/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Police Community Support Officers: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many police community support officers were employed by North Wales Police in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","53246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637953","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The database of Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) is operated by the UK Financial Intelligence Unit, in the National Crime Agency (NCA).</p><p>It is not possible, without further significant analysis which would incur a disproportionate cost, to determine the number of reports in relation to suspected money laundering from Russia.</p><p>The total number of suspicious activity reports filed by sector are listed in the SARs Annual Reports. These are available on the NCA website and the latest report can be found at:</p><p>www.nationalcrimeagency.gov.uk/publications/677-sars-annual-report-2015/file.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-11-23T17:11:29.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637953/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637953/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Money Laundering: Russia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many suspicious activity reports have been filed by UK financial institutions in relation to suspected money laundering conducted from Russia since 2006.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637954","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-11-21","<p>Article 25 of the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations 1961 (VCDR) requires receiving States to &quot;accord full facilities for the performance of the functions of&quot; foreign diplomatic missions. The VCDR is given effect in UK law by the Diplomatic Privileges Act 1964.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-11-21T15:26:06.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637954/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637954/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-11-16","Embassies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will take steps to cut all utility supplies to the Ecuadorian Embassy in London and any other embassy that hosts people who have been charged with committing serious crimes.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","53275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637955","Home Office","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) does not maintain a central record of the nationality or occupation of defendants. This information could only be obtained by examining CPS case files, which would incur disproportionate cost. The number of people prosecuted, convicted and given a custodial sentence for money laundering offences, in England and Wales, from 2010 to 2014 (the latest data available), can be viewed on the Ministry of Justice website at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2014</p><p>under “Criminal justice statistics outcomes by offence data tool”.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-11-23T17:12:22.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637955/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637955/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Money Laundering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether any UK citizens has been prosecuted for acting as a nominee director for a company which has been found to have laundered illicit funds.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637956","Home Office","false","2016-11-29","<p>Investigations into suspected money laundering activities are undertaken by a number of operational agencies in the UK. The specific information requested, in relation to such investigations, is not held centrally.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2016-11-29T17:06:28.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637956/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637956/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-11-16","Money Laundering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether any investigations into UK citizens who hold nominee directorships which pertain to companies suspected of money laundering have been undertaken in the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637957","House of Commons Commission","false","2016-11-22","<p>Ramps for wheelchair users are currently available on the estate for visitors and more can be made available to facilitate access to Members’ offices. The Managing Director of In-House Services will be happy to speak to any hon. Members about their individual needs.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2016-11-22T17:40:52.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637957/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637957/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2016-11-16","Members: Offices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Rt. hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington representing the House of Commons Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 31 October 2016 to Question 51170, if the Commission will purchase ramps for wheelchair users to access those hon. Members' offices that do not yet have step-free access.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","53313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637958","House of Commons Commission","false","2016-11-23","<p>In January of this year the Director of the Digital Service commissioned Deloitte to conduct an independent efficiency review of the Digital Service 10 months after its formation. The top level finding of the review was that: “Parliamentary Digital Service (PDS) is not failing in terms of efficiency for the budget it is allocated and systems it operates, however, it is failing to meet its potential.”</p><p>The review identified eight key themes to improve efficiency and effectiveness: benefits &amp; outcomes, culture, governance, asset management, talent, infrastructure, contracts and strategy. The Digital Service has fully accepted that these are areas for improvement and senior Digital Service staff are taking ownership of these areas.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2016-11-23T11:56:18.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637958/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637958/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2016-11-16","Parliamentary Digital Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Rt. hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, if the House of Commons Commission will undertake a value for money review of the effectiveness of the Parliamentary Digital Service.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","53378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637959","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-23","<p>DFID Pakistan’s education portfolio is designed to provide inclusive education to all children, regardless of their location, gender, religion, or socioeconomic background. DFID has a range of mechanisms which support girls from religious minorities. Through these mechanisms we target girls from religious minorities amongst other groups. DFID liaises with the Pakistan Minorities Teachers Association to understand the needs of teachers and students from minority religions and address them through its various work streams. DFID supports a quota for children from minority religions for higher education scholarships through the Punjab Educational Endowment Fund. The Sindh Education Non State Actors Programme is also building partnerships with non-government schools which aim to reach children from marginalised and minority communities, with a special focus on girls.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-23T17:17:01.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637959/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637959/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Pakistan: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of her Department's education projects in Pakistan in identifying and targeting girls from religious minorities.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","53326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637960","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-23","<p>DFID Pakistan has a range of education projects with elements that support girls from religious minorities. The Punjab Education Support Programme enrols Hindu and Christian girls into non-governmental organisation schools in Muzaffargarh and Rahim Yar Khan in Punjab. The Punjab Education Foundation subsidises schools which prioritise the enrolment of children from minorities. The Sindh Education Non State Actors Programme is reaching children from minority religious communities. DFID’s national education campaign, Alif Ailaan, highlights key issues such as girls’ education and better education for the most marginalised, including minorities. DFID Pakistan’s education portfolio is designed to provide inclusive education to all children, regardless of their location, gender, religion, or socioeconomic background.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-23T17:18:54.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637960/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637960/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Pakistan: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many of her Department's education projects in Pakistan focus on girls from religious minorities.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","53324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637961","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-23","<p>DFID has a range of mechanisms which support girls from religious minorities. DFID liaises with the Pakistan Minorities Teachers Association to understand the needs of teachers and students from minority religions and address them through its various work streams. DFID supports a quota for children from minority religions for higher education scholarships through the Punjab Educational Endowment Fund. The Sindh Education Non State Actors Programme is also building partnerships with non-government schools which aim to reach children from marginalised and minority communities, with a special focus on girls.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-23T17:17:56.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637961/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637961/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Pakistan: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what mechanisms her Department uses to (a) target and (b) support education of girls from religious minorities in Pakistan.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","53325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637962","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-22","<p>The UK has regular discussions with the Government of Malawi on the reforms needed to diversify Malawi’s agricultural base. During my recent visit to Malawi, I urged the Malawian Government to make progress on the policy environment for agribusiness, and particularly emphasised the need for reform to maize markets.</p><p>The UK provides particular support to the expansion of oilseeds and rice as alternative crops. Through the Malawi Innovation Challenge Fund we also support a tea business, and through AgDevCo we invest in groundnuts, sugar, paprika/chillies and macadamia nuts.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-22T14:54:55.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637962/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637962/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Malawi: Crops","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what discussions her Department has had with the government of Malawi on growing alternative crops other than tobacco such as (a) tea and (b) maize.","true","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","53390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637963","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-22","<p>I refer my Rt Hon. Friend to the answer that I gave my Hon. Friend, the Member for Cardiff South and Penarth on 15 September 2016.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-22T16:54:55.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637963/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637963/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637963/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","EU Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what her policy is on the future reallocation of UK aid currently spent through the EU.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637964","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-23","<p>We champion economic development, which is the only way to lift huge numbers of people in poor countries out of poverty. Trade is an important part of economic development. Our economic development work will include support for countries to take advantage of trading opportunities and will not be tied.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-23T17:19:24.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637964/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637964/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Aid Financed Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will take steps to ensure that her Department does not link trade deals to aid projects; and what her policy is on her Department's use of aid to encourage trade deals.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","53293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637965","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-22","<p>For all bilateral education investments, we have developed a range of value for money metrics which track key cost drivers. Where applicable, we use a ‘Payment By Results’ approach which means that programmes such as the Girls’ Education Challenge must demonstrate significant learning improvements for its beneficiaries in order to receive full funding.</p><p>Alongside this, our funding for research projects is building up an evidence base of ‘what works’ to help guarantee that DFID education investments are smart and well-targeted. Scrutiny from the Independent Commission for Aid Impact also ensures that all DFID education investments are as economic, efficient and cost-effective as possible.</p><p>In line with our UK Aid Strategy, we have reviewed all existing spending and have ended projects which are not delivering value for money.</p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-22T14:53:26.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637965/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637965/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Developing Countries: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that her Department achieves value for money in its investment in education.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","53171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637966","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-22","<p>There is a global teacher shortage; at least 74 countries face an acute shortage of teachers. In the period 2011 – 2015 we helped to train 380,000 teachers and improve the effectiveness of teacher development.</p><p>In addition, through our £300 million support to the Global Partnership for Education (GPE), we assist 65 developing countries to develop education sector plans to get trained teachers into classrooms, where they are most needed.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-11-22T14:54:00.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637966/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637966/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Developing Countries: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that her Department supports the recruitment of more teachers in its aid projects.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","53172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637967","Department for International Development","false","2016-11-23","<p>The communications division in Department for International Development monitors content relating to departmental business that is publicly available on social media platforms such as Twitter, Facebook and Instagram. DFID also receives media monitoring services from Precise which incorporate some social media monitoring as part of the package.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-11-23T17:19:54.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637967/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637967/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-11-16","Department for International Development: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department is monitoring content that is publicly available on social networking sites using overt monitoring techniques.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","53231"
