stoms from Concentrix in the last three months have been upheld.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","52935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636999","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-18","<p>As part of the normal tax credits process HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) is reviewing cases where a claimant has made a request for a mandatory reconsideration in light of decisions made by Concentrix.</p><p>HMRC received 32,358 mandatory reconsiderations from Concentrix from 14th September 2016 to 15th November 2016. Ordinarily, the vast majority of mandatory reconsiderations are upheld in the claimant’s favour because new information has come to light during the mandatory reconsideration process. This includes cases where the additional information requested was not originally provided. Of the mandatory reconsiderations processed from Concentrix, 26,990 have been closed with 24,219 (89.7%) of these being upheld in the claimant’s favour. 2,475 of the original 32,358 were wrongly classified as mandatory reconsiderations. The average time taken by HMRC to process mandatory reconsiderations related to tax credits decisions from the point of the request to the final decision between 1st August 2016 and 31st October 2016 was 35.13 days. This includes the time taken to receive any additional information which was not originally provided. HMRC will consider whether a hardship payment is appropriate where one is requested dependent on the circumstances of the specific case. As announced on 7th October, the National Audit Office will be conducting an investigation into HMRC’s contract with Concentrix.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","52933 ; 52934 ; 52935","2016-11-18T14:37:18.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636999/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636999/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/636999/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-15","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average time taken by HM Revenue and Customs staff was to process mandatory reconsiderations requested in relation to tax credit decisions from the point of the request to the final decision in the last three months.","false","Biography information for Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","Ochil and South Perthshire","Ms Tasmina Ahmed-Sheikh","52936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637000","HM Treasury","false","2016-11-23","<p>The table below indicates revenues raised from Vehicle Excise Duty (VED) and fuel duty since financial year 2011-12:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Vehicle Excise Duty collected (£bn)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Fuel duty collected (£bn)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>5.9</p></td><td><p>26.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>6.0</p></td><td><p>26.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>6.0</p></td><td><p>26.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>6.1</p></td><td><p>27.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>5.6</p></td><td><p>27.6</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The Government recognises that fuel costs remain a significant part of business and household costs and at a time when petrol prices are rising and the value of the pound is falling it is important that we focus on the cost of living to ensure we’re protecting the public from any additional costs on their fuel. For this reason, at Autumn Statement 2016, the Government announced the main rate of fuel duty will be frozen for the seventh successive year, saving the average driver £130 every year compared to what they would have been paying under pre-2010 escalator plans.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-11-23T15:53:49.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637000/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637000/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637000/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-11-15","Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was raised for the public purse from (a) Vehicle Excise Duty and (b) Fuel Duty in each year since 2011-12.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","52982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637001","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-23","<p>We are currently considering the findings of this latest research and we plan to publish the report in due course.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-11-23T15:12:44.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637001/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637001/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637001/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when his Department plans to publish the report commissioned from AECOM and Fourwalls in 2015 to monitor air tightness in 55 homes and compliance with Approved Document F in the Building Regulations (Contract Number CPD/004/109/132).","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","52906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637002","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-22","<p>The Department has not spent money specifically targeted on limiting excess winter deaths in the last five years. Through the Local Government Finance Settlement, the department distributes funding to local government. It is for local government to determine how best to manage its own finances to ensure it delivers the appropriate level of services for its residents. Local authorities will be aware of the guidance provided by Public Health England through the Cold Weather plan which makes recommendations for the NHS, public health, social care and other community organisations, to support vulnerable people who have health, housing or economic circumstances that increase their risk of harm.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-11-22T11:57:29.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637002/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637002/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637002/answer","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637002/answer/previousversion/21275","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Death: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department has spent to limit excess winter deaths in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","52940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637003","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-22","<p>Any criteria for council tax equalisation would be developed on a case-by-case basis. The Government remains committed to working with local authorities to keep council tax low for hard-working taxpayers. It has issued no guidance to local authorities considering proposals for reorganisation.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-11-22T11:58:04.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637003/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637003/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637003/answer","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637003/answer/previousversion/21282","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Council Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 14 November 2016 to Question 52130, what criteria the Government applies when considering its approach to council tax equalisation; and whether the Government has issued advice on that subject to local authorities considering proposals for reorganisation.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","52950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637004","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-24","<p>When enacting the Cities and Local Government Act 2016, Parliament agreed the process for conferring powers on a combined authority, including conferring powers on an established combined authority, and there are no plans to seek any change to this.</p>","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy",,"2016-11-24T16:31:01.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637004/answer","Biography information for Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637004/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637004/answer","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637004/answer/previousversion/21279","Biography information for Andrew Percy","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Combined Authorities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if the Government will bring forward legislative proposals to enable the establishment of combined authorities which have the power for extending their functions beyond those initially authorised; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","52954"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637005","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-23","<p>Data on expenditure for training and resources for local emergency services is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy",,"2016-11-23T15:09:25.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637005/answer","Biography information for Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637005/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637005/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Radioactive Materials: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much has been spent on training and resources to enable local emergency services to better respond to possible incidents involving transport of nuclear warheads and high level nuclear waste passing through their areas in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","53089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637006","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-18","<p>Information on the energy efficiency of dwellings is collected through the English Housing Survey. The latest figures (2014) on the number of privately rented properties in each energy efficiency band can be found in AT2.6, published online here: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/501070/2014-15_Section_2_Housing_Stock_tables_and_figures_FINAL.xlsx</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-11-18T13:29:55.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637006/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637006/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637006/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Private Rented Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many properties there are in the private rented sector in each energy efficiency rating.","false","Biography information for Caroline Flint","Don Valley","Caroline Flint","53045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637007","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Shared Ownership and Affordable Homes Programme 2016-21 prospectus was published on 13 April and opened up the programme for bids from private sector providers, including those which are not housing associations, for Shared Ownership. Bidding closed in September and the Homes and Communities Agency is currently considering the bids. Allocations to successful bidders will be announced shortly.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell","53042","2016-11-18T13:52:56.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637007/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637007/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637007/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Affordable Housing: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to enable private sector providers of affordable housing which are not housing associations to be permitted to supply shared equity and other non-traditional housing tenures; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Stewart Jackson","Peterborough","Mr Stewart Jackson","53049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637008","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Shared Ownership and Affordable Homes Programme 2016-21 prospectus was published on 13 April and opened up the programme for bids from private sector providers, including those which are not housing associations, for Shared Ownership. Bidding closed in September and the Homes and Communities Agency is currently considering the bids. Allocations to successful bidders will be announced shortly.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell","53049","2016-11-18T13:52:56.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637008/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637008/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637008/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Affordable Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the Homes and Communities Agency on funding support for private providers of affordable homes which are not classified as registered providers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Stewart Jackson","Peterborough","Mr Stewart Jackson","53042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637009","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-23","<p>My Department has had the following working days lost to mental illness in each of the last three years:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Working Days Lost to Mental Illness</p></td><td><p>Days Lost<br>(Short Term)</p></td><td><p>Days Lost<br>(Long Term)</p></td><td><p>Total Working Days Lost (12 month period)</p></td><td><p>Available Working Days (12 Month Period)</p></td><td><p>% of working days lost due to mental illness</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar-14</p></td><td><p>530</p></td><td><p>1951.5</p></td><td><p>2481.5</p></td><td><p>392905.4</p></td><td><p>0.6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar-15</p></td><td><p>753.0</p></td><td><p>1849.0</p></td><td><p>2602.0</p></td><td><p>389052.2</p></td><td><p>0.7%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar-16</p></td><td><p>733.5</p></td><td><p>2959</p></td><td><p>3692.5</p></td><td><p>389960.2</p></td><td><p>0.9%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct-16</p></td><td><p>588</p></td><td><p>2986.5</p></td><td><p>3574.5</p></td><td><p>365433.4</p></td><td><p>1.0%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The department introduced Mental Health First Aid training for staff in February 2015 and has since trained over 100 people. We have an active Mental Health Ambassador Network of staff who offer advice, support and direction to both staff and managers. DCLG also has also a Mental Health Support Group that encourages staff experiencing poor mental health or who caring for someone with a mental health illness to share experiences and offer mutual support and advice.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-11-23T17:50:57.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637009/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637009/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637009/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Department for Communities and Local Government: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what number of working days were lost due to mental illness in his Department in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","53064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637010","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-18","<p>We remain committed to the Voluntary Right to Buy for housing association tenants and the pilot scheme is informing the design of the main scheme. The Government is continuing to work closely with the National Housing Federation and the housing association sector on the implementation of the main scheme and will announce more details in due course.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-11-18T13:28:05.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637010/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637010/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637010/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Right to Buy Scheme: Housing Associations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what progress has been made on ensuring that all registered social housing association tenants have the right to buy their own homes since the conclusion of the pilot scheme.","false","Biography information for Oliver Colvile","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Oliver Colvile","53037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637011","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-23","<p>The Government's strategy to better meet the needs of employers, learners and local areas is to establish a skills system that is responsive to local economic needs. For those combined authorities with signed devolution deals this means assuming responsibility for the Adult Education Budget (AEB) in 2018/19, enabling them to commission outcomes which deliver the skills needed locally. Devolution deals in the North of England all include full devolution of AEB from 2018/19, enabling areas of the North to tackle their local skills shortages.</p>","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy",,"2016-11-23T15:11:51.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637011/answer","Biography information for Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637011/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637011/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Skilled Workers: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of devolution of the adult skills budget on reducing the skills shortage in the North of England.","false","Biography information for Graham Evans","Weaver Vale","Graham Evans","53016"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637012","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-23","<p>We remain committed to the Voluntary Right to Buy for housing association tenants. The Government is continuing to work closely with the National Housing Federation and the housing association sector on the implementation of the main scheme and will announce more details in due course.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2016-11-23T15:12:17.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637012/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637012/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637012/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Right to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the timetable is for the roll-out of the Right to Buy scheme nationally.","false","Biography information for Michael Tomlinson","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Michael Tomlinson","53128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637013","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-23","<p>Police forces are always notified in advance of a nuclear weapon convoy being routed through their area. Police forces may advise fire and rescue services of the presence of the convoy if it is moving into the vicinity of a fire service operation. I am withholding specific information on the period of notice given to emergency services as its disclosure would prejudice the capability, effectiveness and security of the armed forces.</p><p>The Ministry of Defence holds no High Level Waste as part of the Defence Nuclear Programme.</p><p>For those movements of civil nuclear and radioactive material that the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy is responsible for, the relevant police authorities are involved in the planning stages and are aware of upcoming movements of material. The other emergency services are involved on a case by case basis, but for higher category material, all three emergency services sit in the Multi-Agency Command Centre and will be aware movements are due to take place.</p>","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy",,"2016-11-23T15:08:51.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637013/answer","Biography information for Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637013/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637013/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-11-15","Radioactive Materials: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what notice is given to local government emergency services on nuclear warhead convoys and consignments of high level nuclear waste passing through their areas.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","53088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637014","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-18","<p>Sport England use the Active People Survey to monitor participation.</p><p> </p><p>In May 2016, Sport England published its new strategy, 'Towards an Active Nation' that sets out how future investment in grassroots sport will be made. It includes an investment guide to all National Governing Bodies (NGB) for the 2017-21 period.Previous track record of delivery against targets in the 2013-2017 funding cycle will be part of that assessment. The NGB investment guide is available on Sport England’s website: <a href="https://www.sportengland.org/our-work/national-governing-bodies/investment-guide/" target="_blank">https://www.sportengland.org/our-work/national-governing-bodies/investment-guide/</a></p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-11-18T12:29:16.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637014/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637014/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637014/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-15","Football: Public Participation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how her Department monitors the Football Association's effectiveness in maintaining participation numbers of people playing football; and what account her Department takes of such numbers in future funding decisions.","false","Biography information for Richard Graham","Gloucester","Richard Graham","53057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637015","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The integrity of sport is absolutely paramount, and the new UK Sports Governance code published last month - part of our 'Sporting Future' strategy - is clear that we expect the highest standards of governance and transparency from all our sports governing bodies that want to receive public funding in future. Among the requirements is that organisations have strong leadership in place, with the right checks and balances to minimise the likelihood of integrity issues arising.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-11-18T12:29:50.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637015/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637015/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637015/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-15","Football: Corruption","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether the Government plans to undertake any further action to prevent corruption within football.","false","Biography information for Richard Graham","Gloucester","Richard Graham","53058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637016","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-23","<p>The number of working days lost in the Department for Culture, Media and Sport due to all illness reported under the Mental &amp; Behavioural Disorders category in each of the last three years is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Working days lost</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 March 2013 to 31 March 2014</p></td><td><p>305</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 March 2014 to 31 March 2015</p></td><td><p>189</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 March 2015 to 31 March 2016</p></td><td><p>79</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>We provide support to help all employees to stay well and manage their health conditions at work. This support includes a variety of programmes like occupational health support, the Employee Assistance Programme and the Civil Service reasonable adjustments service.</p><p>We signed up to level 2 of the Disability Confident Scheme and the “Time to Change” pledge and have been actively working with line managers to support individuals with mental health conditions. We introduced Mental Health First Aiders who are trained to recognise the symptoms of mental health and guide the individual towards appropriate professional help.</p><p>These actions have led to a continued decrease in the number of working days lost due to mental health sickness absence.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-11-23T11:39:58.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637016/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637016/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637016/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-15","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many working days were lost due to mental illness in her Department in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","53065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637017","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Government recognises the importance of tackling childhood obesity, which is caused by a number of complex factors. The Childhood Obesity Plan for Action, published in August, considered a number of different policy responses to address this problem. Additional advertising restrictions were considered as part of this process, but current restrictions in the UK are amongst the toughest in the world and the plan focuses on those areas which experts tell us are most effective.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-11-18T14:26:47.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637017/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637017/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637017/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-15","Television: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect of restricting High in Fat, Salt or Sugar (HFSS) food advertising during all programmes before the 9pm watershed relative to existing restrictions on such advertising on (a) children's exposure to HFSS food and (b) children's obesity rates.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","53041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637018","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The BBC published their Diversity Strategy in April of this year. In the White Paper; A BBC for the Future: a broadcaster for distinction, the Government welcomed the proposals set out in the Diversity Strategy. The Government is confident that the BBC will fulfil its remit to serve all audiences and ensure that it will make suitable provisions to ensure that everyone can access their services.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-11-18T14:27:31.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637018/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637018/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637018/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-15","BBC: Video on Demand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will discuss with the BBC Trust what steps it plans to take to support people with visual impairments to register for the BBC iPlayer service ahead of the new registration requirement expected to be introduced in 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","52930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637019","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-11-18","<p>The Commission has liaised closely with the financial services sector during the course of its work, to identify potential new dormant assets and the projected size of the funding pot that can be used to support good causes once all attempts to reunite customers with their assets has failed. Its findings and recommendations will be published in due course.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-11-18T12:15:55.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637019/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637019/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637019/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-11-15","Dormant Assets Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what progress the Dormant Assets Commission has made since it was established in March 2016.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","52931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637020","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-18","<p>Type 45 Destroyers are supported by an In Service Support Contract between the Ministry of Defence and BAE Systems, delivering a range of support activity which includes defect rectification. Type 45 defect rectification activity is predominately supported by specific Contracts For Availability with the Original Equipment Manufacturers. These contracts include specific incentives to ensure effective and cost efficient defect rectification, and they are assessed against performance and cost on a regular basis.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-11-18T14:18:20.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637020/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637020/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637020/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-15","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the (a) effectiveness and (b) cost efficiency of the system for repair of defects on the UK's Type 45 destroyers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","52945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637021","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-11-18","<p>All NATO Allies have a collective responsibility to monitor the path and activity of non-NATO ships passing through NATO areas of responsibility. The UK fully upholds its commitments in this regard and will act accordingly.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-11-18T14:17:54.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637021/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637021/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/637021/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-11-15","Russia: Territorial Waters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether it is his policy that Royal Navy warships should always escort ships of the Russian Navy when they are within UK waters.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","52944"
